Section 12: Spring Security
    Lecture 73: Spring Security Roles

1. Add Roles
 1.1 SpringJPABootstrap.java
    - ej.springframework.bootstrap.SpringJPABootstrap.java
    - Add Role in the loadRoles()
 1.2 Start Spring Boot Server
 1.3 Connect H2 DB Server
    - http://localhost:8080/h2-console
    - login and check the testdb tables
      ( ** Note: If you have a login trouble with h2 db, after login so You have to add below two line in
       the ej.springframework.config.SpringSecConfig.java

       http.csrf().disable();
       http.headers().frameOptions().disable();
       )
    - check USER_ROLE table that added to role 2

2. Spring Configuration:
  - ej.springframework.config.SpringSecConfig.java
 2.1 Add .hasRole("ADMIN")
 2.2 Rebuild project
 2.3 Start Server
 2.4 Login fglenanne / password --> User menu